Class BasicCachePlugin

java.lang.Object
  org.dmd.dmp.server.servlet.base.DmpServletPlugin
      org.dmd.dmp.server.servlet.base.plugins.BasicCachePlugin
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Runnable, DmcNameResolverIF, CacheIF, DmcUncheckedOIFHandlerIF
public class BasicCachePlugin
extends DmpServletPlugin
implements CacheIF, java.lang.Runnable, DmcUncheckedOIFHandlerIF

The BasicCachePlugin provides the implementation of a cache of objects that are the focus of your data management application. The design of a cache is often quite application specific, so the way that this cache works may not be suitable to your needs; it is merely an example of how such a cache could work.

The cache supports the basic CRUDE mechanism (not just CRUD - see the Dark Matter Data Overview page - http://code.google.com/p/dark-matter-data/wiki/DMDOverview). The 'E' stands for events.

maintainIndex

public void maintainIndex(DmcClassInfo ci)
Description copied from interface: CacheIF
Indexing is a generally useful mechanism that allows for rapid access to objects of a particular type. This method should be overloaded to add an index for the specified class. This mechanism should work for both concrete and abstract classes since it is easy to determine if a DMO is an instance of a particular base class using the DmcClassInfo.isInstanceOf() method.

Specified by:

public DmcNamedObjectIF findNamedObject(DmcObjectName name,
                                        int attributeID)
Description copied from interface: DmcNameResolverIF
Finds a named object based on its name and indicates the attribute via which the reference is being made. This method is used via the DmcObject and is primarily intended to handle the situation where we must resolve internal type definitions as opposed to class definitions. This is due to the fact that we create internal type definitions for classes that have the same name as the associated classes.
